users/tanghus","html_url":"https://github.com/tanghus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-03-12t10:35:51z","updated_at":"2013-03-12t10:35:51z","body":"the realm would also have to be the same i.e. `owncloud`. i doubt that it will work though, but you are free to try ;)"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/15010852","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/107#issuecomment-15010852","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/107","id":15010852,"user":{"login":"ibboard","id":388582,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/a3feccaf052a8282c1cfcc9549a7151e?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f405ba9d1e05cabc9fadac704bfa594b4.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"a3feccaf052a8282c1cfcc9549a7151e","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard","html_url":"https://github.com/ibboard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-03-16t19:37:55z","updated_at":"2013-03-16t19:37:55z","body":"i've just tried using apache http auth and it seems to work fine. owncloud is in my root dir for the domain and i've got:\r\n\r\n    <location />\r\n        authtype basic\r\n        authname \"owncloud\"\r\n        authuserfile /path/to/owncloud.htpasswd\r\n        require valid-user\r\n    </location>\r\n\r\nthe only limitation will be that you can't manage users from within owncloud at the moment, but as i'm just using the system for myself then that is fine (and is probably okay for some other people as well)."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/15011414","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/107#issuecomment-15011414","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/107","id":15011414,"user":{"login":"tanghus","id":533222,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/e625b634822713b2e346ff7c67d26775?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f6d9c90af1c12f5a88e4d5f216bbc1979.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"e625b634822713b2e346ff7c67d26775","url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus","html_url":"https://github.com/tanghus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-03-16t20:14:11z","updated_at":"2013-03-16t20:14:11z","body":"it's been a long time since i messed with web server setup, but i seem to remember it was possible to use custom auth backends?"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/15011769","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/107#issuecomment-15011769","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/107","id":15011769,"user":{"login":"ibboard","id":388582,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/a3feccaf052a8282c1cfcc9549a7151e?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f405ba9d1e05cabc9fadac704bfa594b4.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"a3feccaf052a8282c1cfcc9549a7151e","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard","html_url":"https://github.com/ibboard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibboard/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-03-16t20:36:04z","updated_at":"2013-03-16t21:03:12z","body":"you can change the apache auth backend (the \"authtype\"), but based on what i'd read then i assumed it only worked with \"basic\", but it does appear to work with \"digest\" as well:\r\n\r\n    <location />\r\n                authtype digest\r\n                authname \"owncloud\"\r\n                authdigestdomain /\r\n                authuserfile /path/to/owncloud.htdigest\r\n                require valid-user\r\n    </location>\r\n\r\nand then create users with htdigest command.\r\n\r\nit'd be good if owncloud could manage it as well (trac can be configured to control user accounts in .htdigest files) but unless i'm missing something then i've not seen anything so far.\r\n\r\n\r\n[edit] although not everything supports digest. i tested with chrome accessing the web side and it was fine, but 20 minutes later thunderbird refreshed itself and lightning or the sogo connector prompted me for login details and wouldn't accept them until i change the web server back to basic auth (over ssl)."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/15012927","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/107#issuecomment-15012927","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/107","id":15012927,"user":{"login":"tanghus","id":533222,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/e625b634822713b2e346ff7c67d26775?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f6d9c90af1c12f5a88e4d5f216bbc1979.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"e625b634822713b2e346ff7c67d26775","url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus","html_url":"https://github.com/tanghus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tanghus/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-03-16t21:55:46z","updated_at":"2013-03-16t21:55:46z","body":"i was more thinking about using auth_mysql and authenticate against the owncloud db - but no idea if it would work, just a thought ;)"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/18547632","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/107#issuecomment-18547632","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/107","id":18547632,"user":{"login":"renneb","id":4548652,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/0eb824e78e77875a2ad73f9811b8a5d2?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fb6a386062391b26affe710b30a952208.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"0eb824e78e77875a2ad73f9811b8a5d2","url":"https://api.github.com/users/renneb","html_url":"https://github.com/renneb","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/renneb/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/renneb/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/renneb/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/renneb/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/renneb/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/renneb/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/renneb/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/renneb/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/renneb/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-05-28t12:42:30z","updated_at":"2013-05-28t12:42:30z","body":"in oc 5.0.6 i've found a workaround.\r\n\r\nwe've system-wide https-basic-authentication via apache/pwauth\r\n\r\n\\<directory /var/www/>\r\n\t\tauthtype\t\t       basic\r\n\t\tauthname                private\r\n\t\tauthbasicprovider\texternal\r\n\t\tauthexternal\t\tpwauth\r\n\t\toptions indexes followsymlinks multiviews\r\n\t\tallowoverride all\r\n\t\torder allow,deny\r\n\t\tallow from all\r\n                require valid-user\r\n\\</directory>\r\naddexternalauth\t\tpwauth\t/usr/sbin/pwauth\r\nsetexternalauthmethod\tpwauth\tpipe\r\n\r\n\r\nif username and passwort in the oc database match username and password of a system-user, he's logged in automagically. but if the password in the oc database doesn't match the basic-authenticated password, the login form is shown with the \"lost password?\" message.\r\n\r\nobviously oc checks $_server['php_auth_user'] and $_server['php_auth_pw'], but instead of just using $_server['php_auth_user'] it tries to login internally with $_server['php_auth_pw'].\r\n\r\nas i haven't found the corresponding oc-code, yet, i tried to write a new authentication class (http://forum.owncloud.org/viewtopic.php?f=23&t=11472&p=29743&hilit=renne#p29743), but it failed to to anything. :(\r\n\r\nas a workaround i installed the user_unix-app which uses pwauth, too, to make sure oc uses the same passwords like apache. it's dirty, but it works - for now.\r\n\r\nit would be great, if oc wouldn't check the password if a user is already authenticated via http(s)."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/21158533","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/107#issuecomment-21158533","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/107","id":21158533,"user":{"login":"tamaskan","id":3661769,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/0fec1f2f7f23e3fa79e782f353e62d7a?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f7219eb2236f9ee7015299de300b56d20.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"0fec1f2f7f23e3fa79e782f353e62d7a","url":"https://api.github.com/users/tamaskan","html_url":"https://github.com/tamaskan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tamaskan/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tamaskan/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tamaskan/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tamaskan/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tamaskan/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tamaskan/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tamaskan/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tamaskan/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tamaskan/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-07-18t02:13:50z","updated_at":"2013-07-18t02:13:50z","body":"the code you are looking for should be in ./lib/base.php"}]